<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Size</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> - Size does matter! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Your signature graphic should not be excessively wide or tall, causing deformation of formatting and layout. <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  600 pixels in width and 250 pixels in height</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> should be more than sufficient (actually, the smaller the width, the better, since we use an smaller format than most generic EzBoards). Your signature graphic should be <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  no larger than 15 KB</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> in size (animated gifs and flash sigs too). If you currently have a &quot;big sig&quot;, try clipping it, scaling it down, or increasing the level of compression (for JPEG files).<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Etiquette</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> - Don't use your medium-to-large graphical signature if your post is shorter than your sig, or if you're posting for the second (or third or fourth...) time in the same thread - readers have already seen it; this is simply good etiquette. You can temporarily disable your sig in a single post by checking the box at the bottom in the section marked &quot;posting options.&quot;<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Testing</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> - We have a forum specifically for testing and showing off artwork, html, sigs and pics. It's called &quot;The Comics&quot; - please use it, or use the &quot;preview&quot; feature, so we don't have to move your posts and the normal boards don't become cluttered with testing posts.<br>
<br>
If we all follow these guidelines, everyone can enjoy MMDN without waiting an age for the pages to load, AND readers will be able to savor your sigs rather than be sick to death of seeing them 80 times in one thread. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub18.ezboard.com/ummdn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MMDN</A> at: 8/2/01 7:35:11 am<br></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub18.ezboard.com/fmithanielmarrdailynewsfrm30.showMessage?topicID=7.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub18.ezboard.com/fmithanielmarrdailynewsfrm30.showMessage?topicID=11.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub18.ezboard.com/fmithanielmarrdailynewsfrm30.emailToFriend?topicID=9.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub18.ezboard.com/fmithanielmarrdailynewsfrm30.threadControl?topicID=9.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub18.ezboard.com/fmithanielmarrdailynewsfrm30.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=9.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub18.ezboard.com/fmithanielmarrdailynewsfrm30.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=9.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub18.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select na